'''Missile cruiser''' was a term used to describe ships belonging to one of the myriad [[Cruiser/Legends|cruiser]] classes whose primary armament consisted of missile launchers rather than energy weapons or along side them.

==History==
Well known classes in the missile cruiser role included the purpose-built [[Broadside-class cruiser kdb-1|''Broadside''-class cruiser kdb-1]] and the modified [[Marauder-class Assault Corvette/Legends|''Marauder''-class corvette]].<ref name="EAW">''[[Star Wars: Empire at War]]''</ref> Some variants of both the [[Consular-class light cruiser/Legends|''Consular''-class space cruiser]]<ref name="SOTG07">[[Starships of the Galaxy (Saga Edition)|''Starships of the Galaxy'', Saga Edition]]</ref> and the [[ShaShore-class frigate|Galactic Alliance frigate]]<ref name="Legacy0">[[Star Wars: Legacy (2006) 0½|''Star Wars: Legacy'' (2006) 0½]]</ref> were modified to serve as missile cruisers.

